            <scopecontent>
                <p>This collection consists primarily of travel diaries kept by Anna Albertson
                    Collins (Mrs. Lester Collins) on her numerous trips abroad between 1909 and
                    1965. Diaries include photographs and postcards, clippings, brochures, and
                    stamps. The entries record daily activities and sights seen. The collection also
                    includes arithmetic books of Chalkley and John Albertson (1780s), diaries of
                    Elisabeth and Anna Swift (1830s-1850s), a book of verses belonging to Jane Swift
                    (1830s), commonplace books (1834-1835), and a book of notes on businesses and
                    recipes (1850s). </p>
            </scopecontent>

